### Test CampusLost API Endpoints

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "registerNo": "22CSE1001",
  "name": "John Smith",
  "department": "CSE",
  "college": "ABC University",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Login with the user
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get all items (no authentication required)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/items

### 4. Create a lost item (requires authentication)
# First run the login request above to get the JWT token
# Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE with the actual token from login response
POST http://localhost:8081/api/items
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "title": "Lost Blue Wallet",
  "description": "Leather wallet with student ID and credit cards",
  "category": "Accessories",
  "status": "LOST",
  "location": "Library",
  "contactInfo": "Call 9876543210"
}

### 5. Create a found item (requires authentication)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/items
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "title": "Found iPhone 14",
  "description": "Black iPhone with cracked screen",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "status": "FOUND",
  "location": "Computer Lab",
  "contactInfo": "WhatsApp: 9876543210"
}

### 6. Search items by keyword
GET http://localhost:8081/api/items/search?keyword=wallet

### 7. Filter items by status
GET http://localhost:8081/api/items/status/LOST

### 8. Get user's items (requires authentication)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/items/my
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 9. Advanced filtering
GET http://localhost:8081/api/items/filter?status=LOST&category=Electronics&keyword=phone

### 10. Get recent items
GET http://localhost:8081/api/items/recent

### 11. Update an item (requires authentication and ownership)
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/items/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "title": "Lost Blue Wallet - UPDATED",
  "description": "Leather wallet with student ID, credit cards, and driver's license",
  "category": "Accessories",
  "status": "LOST",
  "location": "Library - 2nd Floor",
  "contactInfo": "Call 9876543210 or email john@example.com"
}

### 12. Delete an item (requires authentication and ownership)
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/items/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
